    "heading": "Big percents and tiny percents",
    "intro": "<p><strong>100% = one whole.</strong> A percent over 100 is more than a whole; a percent under 1 is a sliver. To turn a percent into a decimal, divide by 100 (slide the dot 2 places left).</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>200% = 2.00 = 2 wholes.</strong> 150% = 1.5 = one and a half.",
      "<strong>0.5% = 0.005</strong> — much smaller than 1%. (0.5 ÷ 100 = 0.005.)"
    ]
